==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Dirigent
<hw>Dir"i*gent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>The line of
motion along which a describent line or surface is carried in the
genesis of any plane or solid figure; a directrix.</def>
<rj><au>Hutton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dirigible</ent>⟦br⟧
